            <h4>What is the current population of Follansbee?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Follansbee is 2,799.  Follansbee, West Virginia is the 6,475th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            

            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Follansbee?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Follansbee was in
                    1990, when its population was
                    3,328.
                    
                        In 1990, Follansbee was the
                        5,199th largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 6,475th largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Follansbee is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            15.9%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 1990.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Follansbee shrinking?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Follansbee has shrunk
                        9.8% 
                        since the year 2000.
                    


                    
                        Follansbee, West Virginia's growth is extremely below
                        average.
                        86% of similarly sized
                        cities are growing faster since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
