                <h4>What is the voting age population of Follansbee, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Follansbee, West Virginia, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 2,246.  The voting age population is 47.9% male and 52.1% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Follansbee, West Virginia residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 23.7% of
                        the residents of Follansbee are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Follansbee, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Follansbee are 96.3% White, 2.2% Two or more races and 1.5% Other. Additionally, 1.5% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Follansbee, West Virginia residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Follansbee, 14.1% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 22.4%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    11.3% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Follansbee.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Follansbee, West Virginia residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 55.4% of
                    Follansbee residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Follansbee, West Virginia residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    88.9% of
                    Follansbee residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 19.0%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 6.0%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Follansbee, West Virginia residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Follansbee residents aged 5 and older, 2.8% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                1.2% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                1.6% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.0% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Follansbee, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Follansbee is 3.9%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
